# Members database (Neon Postgres)

- Member login data is in Postgres (`members`, `password_resets`), not Firestore.
- Use `db.members` or `routes.member_store`; never introduce new Firestore `Members` reads/writes.
- Schema: `db/schema.sql`. Human docs: `docs/DATABASE.md`.
- Passwords: bcrypt only; strip passwords from all API JSON.
- Scripts: `scripts/db/apply_schema.py`, `scripts/db/migrate_from_firebase.py`, `scripts/db/set_admin.py`.
- Other collections (Events, Meeting, …) remain Firebase until explicitly migrated.
